The paper discusses the development and validation of a software fault prediction model using ensemble methods and source code metrics. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) as it deals with improving the software development process. The use of ensemble methods also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also mentions the selection of input metrics, which could fall under software development (cs.SD) or programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the evaluation of the fault prediction model could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) as it deals with identifying and preventing potential faults in software.
